 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of resource management capabilities.
   </p>
   <p>The following capabilities is provided by the resource management module:
   <ul>
   <li>Resource availability may be specified by quantity and location
   </li>
   <li>Resource provision, allocation and issuing events may be scheduled and recorded
   </li>
   <li>Future resource provisions may be designated to specific locations
   </li>
   <li>Relationships between planned and actual resource events may be recorded
   </li>
   <li>Relationships between resource event and the corresponding resource requirement, usage or consumption may be recorded.
   </li>
   </ul>
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>Resource availability</li>
   <li>Scheduling and recording of resource provision, allocation and issuing</li>
   <li>Relationships between allocated resources and the corresponding resource requirements</li>
   <li>Relationships between issued resources and the corresponding resource record.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>Identification and detailed descriptions of managed resources</li>
   <li>Resource requirement specification</li>
   <li>Recording resource usage or consumption.</li>
 </outscope>

